Use of the hybridization in situ method in the detection of human papillomaviruses in female genital tumor tissue. We review preliminary results obtained by use of this diagnostic procedure--hybridization in situ for diagnosis of human papilloma virus in bioptic material of anogenital tract in women. Of 11 examined bioptic specimens, we found positive hybridization signal on "test" groups HPV 6, 11 and HPV 16, 18. This is the first report on papilloma virus in women from the territory of Vojvodina.